(firstQuint)Prevalence of Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease in Peritoneal Dialysis and Hemodialysis Patients.

 Gastroesophageal reflux disease is a common upper gastrointestinal disorder in chronic kidney disease.

 But, little is known about the prevalence in dialysis patients.

 The aims of this study were to determine the prevalence of GERD among chronic kidney disease with peritoneal dialysis and hemodialysis in Korea.

